SkyComment: For the sky conditions, I thought it was pretty clear with the occasional cloud that would move out of the way given a little time. I found that it was slightly hard to adjust to the sky and ended up staying outside an extra 15 minutes just to try to get adjusted. I was not sure if that was from the street lights however or that the sky was just not as clear that night.
LocationComment: I would say that this location was pretty good however not great. I chose to go at the fifty-yard line of the football practice field on the side closer to the stadium. I wanted to go inside the stadium for pitch black surrounding however unfortunately they lock the stadium. I would say that there was not a lot of light pollution and it really only came from the street lights on the other side.

SkyComment: I found that the clouds tonight were slightly worse than the previous night however the sky was much clearer at times. While waiting for the cloud to move I was able to spot the big dipper I believe which was very cool. When the clouds did move I was pretty clearly able to see Denebola and the surrounding stars. I thought I was able to get a pretty good picture of the constellation after looking.
LocationComment: While looking SW from the tennis courts it was incredibly easy to get my eyes adjusted due to the fact there were minimal lights blocking my view. I started on the far side of the courts however after locating the constellation Leo I chose to move towards the center in order to get a better angle(there were some tall trees a little in my way).
